  "_design_notes": "v8.13.1 orchestrator subagent profile. The orchestrator subagent is spawned by scripts/run-cycle.sh and constrained by three PreToolUse hooks (ship-gate, phase-gate-precondition, role-gate). allowed_tools is intentionally narrow: orchestrator can RUN scripts (via Bash(bash scripts/...:*)) but cannot Edit/Write source code (that's Builder's job inside a worktree — role-gate enforces) and cannot directly invoke git commit/push/gh release create (must go through scripts/ship.sh which ship-gate allowlists). Phase ordering is enforced by phase-gate-precondition: subagent-run.sh invocations must respect the Scout→Builder→Auditor sequence in cycle-state.json. v8.13.1 audit MEDIUM-1 fix: cycle-state.sh permissions are restricted to {advance,set-agent,get,exists,dump,path} subcommands; init+clear are denied so the orchestrator cannot self-disable the gates by removing cycle-state.json. run-cycle.sh's parent process (NOT the orchestrator subagent) handles init/clear lifecycle. v8.19.3: each kernel-script pattern has BOTH a relative variant (Bash(bash scripts/...:*) — works in dev mode where cwd=repo) AND a glob-absolute variant (Bash(bash **/scripts/...:*) — works in plugin install mode where the orchestrator uses $EVOLVE_PLUGIN_ROOT/scripts/... after the v8.18.0 dual-root migration). The same dual-pattern approach applies to disallowed_tools so the bypass-prevention guards continue working.",
